name: Cu+-exporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + Cu+[side 1] = ADP + phosphate + Cu+[side 2] [RN:R00086]
comment: A P-type ATPase that undergoes covalent phosphorylation during the transport cycle. This enzyme transports Cu+ or Ag+, and cannot transport the divalent ions, contrary to EC 3.6.3.4, Cu2+-exporting ATPase, which mainly transports the divalent copper ion.
